data.name: syncOptionBox.ToolTip
data.value: This sets the behavior of the sync. Merge Prompt: This will ask you which contact to overwrite if both have been updated. Merge Outlook Wins: If both contacts have been updated, the Google contact will be overwritten. Merge Google Wins: If both contacts have been updated, the Outlook contact will be overwritten. Outlook To Google Only: Only updates Google contacts based on outlook contacts. Google To Outlook Only: Only updates Outlook contacts based on google contacts.

data.name: btPromptDelete.ToolTip
data.value: This specifies whether the user shall be asked before an entry is deleted. Enabling this option means if you delete a contact from Google and the sync starts afterwards, then you will be asked, if the according entry shall be deleted from Outlook and vice versa.

data.name: proxySettingsLinkLabel.ToolTip
data.value: By default the systems proxy settings are used. Go to Internet Explorer Settings and setup the proxy in the LAN Configuration. If alternate configuration is required or default setting does not work, click this link.
